A U.S. Capitol Police Officer named William Evans was killed in an act of violence, while another officer is in critical condition. The incident occurred while Officer Evans was protecting the Capitol. The article expresses condolences to Officer Evans' family and those who knew him. The authors are grateful for the Capitol Police, the National Guard Immediate Response Force, and others who responded quickly to the attack. They also commend the bravery of the men and women defending the Capitol, particularly in light of recent violent incidents.